get_value() -> activecontexttypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, discovery of types for `session.client` and `session.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) project page for "types-aiobotocore-lexv2-models" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. This package provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.LexModelsV2 service, compatible with various IDEs and tools like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, mypy, and pyright. It's generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2. The package aims to help developers find and fix potential bugs by offering explicit type annotations, client annotations, waiters annotations, literals, and type definitions. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package supports automated type annotation updates for aiobotocore services, ensuring coverage for all available services and providing up-to-date documentation for each class and method. Installation instructions, usage examples, and information on how to contribute or report issues are also provided.
